{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/adversarial-drum-synthesis/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Jake Drysdale"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"3344250b-7a70-52fd-a819-1053510f616d","excerpt":"Drysdale, J. and Tomczak, M. and J. Hockman. 2020. Adversarial synthesis of drum sounds. In Proceedings of the 23nd International Conference on Digital Audio…","html":"<p>Drysdale, J. and Tomczak, M. and J. Hockman. 2020. Adversarial synthesis of drum sounds. In Proceedings of the 23nd International Conference on Digital Audio Effects, Vienna, Austria.</p>\n<p>[<a href=\"https://dafx2020.mdw.ac.at/proceedings/papers/DAFx2020_paper_45.pdf\">pdf</a>,\n<a href=\"https://dafx2020.mdw.ac.at/proceedings/presentations/paper_45.mp4\">presentation</a>]</p>\n<p>Recent advancements in generative audio synthesis have allowed for the development of creative tools for generation and manipulation of audio.\nIn this project, a strategy is proposed for the synthesis of drum sounds using generative adversarial networks (GANs).\nThe system is based on a conditional Wasserstein GAN, which learns the underlying probability distribution of a dataset compiled of labeled drum sounds.\nLabels are used to condition the system on an integer value that can be used to generate audio with the desired characteristics.\nSynthesis is controlled by an input latent vector that enables continuous exploration and interpolation of generated waveforms.</p>\n<center><h3>Audio Examples</h3></center>\n<p>Results accompanying the paper “Adversarial Synthesis of Drum sounds” for the International Conference on Digital Audio Effects 2020.</p>\n<h1><center></h1>\n<h4>Training Data</h4>\n<p>A random selection of 30 examples from the dataset used in training.</p>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Kick drums</figcaption>\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/05edad88151533603b2e2865b127a154/realkicks.wav\">\n\t</audio>\n</figure>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Snare drums</figcaption>\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/fb3448edbddb484fe4b80b6ff71b72ba/realsnares.wav\">\n\t</audio>\n</figure>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Cymbals</figcaption>\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/e9c7ad2dc9ff9de6ef401966f57c0856/realcymbals.wav\">\n\t</audio>\n</figure>\n<h4>Generations</h4>\n<p>A random selection of 30 examples from the generated data.</p>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Kick drums</figcaption>\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/43eb2ebfb4e9c6466622a6506cadd1ae/genkicks.wav\">\n\t</audio>\n</figure>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Snare drums</figcaption>\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/8dac81c07daab7aa8b7c5845fb4227e8/gensnares.wav\">\n\t</audio>\n</figure>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Cymbals</figcaption>\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/5b93f5a5d414072d2e38bc9c706f9247/gencymbals.wav\">\n\t</audio>\n</figure>\n<h4>Usage demonstration</h4>\n<p>Example usage within loop-based electronic music compositions.\nThe percussive elements of the following tracks were created using a selection\nof samples from the generated data. A light amount of post-processing (equalisation and volume envelope shaping)\nwas applied to mix the sounds.</p>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Track 1: Hip hop demo</figcaption>\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/7da59eabcb45b5231b0d5426173c21fa/hiphopdemo.wav\">\n\t</audio>\n</figure>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Track 2: Drum and bass demo</figcaption>\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/94ea879a4cd8db0512786e42af715ab8/drumandbassdemo.wav\">\n\t</audio>\n</figure>\n<h5>Generating Drum Loops</h5>\n<p>Below are some examples of the systems capacity to generate 1 bar loops. A dataset of 130bpm, 1 bar drum loops was complied and then sliced into 16th note segments. The system is conditioned on each of these segments (giving a total of 16 classes) and then trained for a number of iterations. A loop can be created by generating a waveform for each of the 16 classes and then concatentating them together. </p>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/blog/static/7ce76149a500650673556cbd320a7957/9937c/generation-conditions.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 18.91891891891892%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"drawing\" title=\"drawing\" src=\"/blog/static/7ce76149a500650673556cbd320a7957/fcda8/generation-conditions.png\" srcset=\"/blog/static/7ce76149a500650673556cbd320a7957/12f09/generation-conditions.png 148w,\n/blog/static/7ce76149a500650673556cbd320a7957/e4a3f/generation-conditions.png 295w,\n/blog/static/7ce76149a500650673556cbd320a7957/fcda8/generation-conditions.png 590w,\n/blog/static/7ce76149a500650673556cbd320a7957/efc66/generation-conditions.png 885w,\n/blog/static/7ce76149a500650673556cbd320a7957/9937c/generation-conditions.png 1156w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Training loop example 1</figcaption>\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/78e0959df1fb5f3cea0f752083e7ebc3/train11.wav\">\n\t</audio>\n</figure>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Training loop example 2</figcaption>\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/b46f9403a396ad96ae8dc9ef7d23b2d7/train12.wav\">\n\t</audio>\n</figure>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Generated loop example 1</figcaption>\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/f4d2f55e105fd1da11b84533c119de52/gen11.wav\">\n\t</audio>\n</figure>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Generated loop example 2</figcaption>\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/ad9aa27b24b6abc6281736071b53e6ab/gen12.wav\">\n\t</audio>\n</figure>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Interpolating between two different loops</figcaption>\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/8137e551cf407c6e65ed66c5b9a63b74/slerp1.wav\">\n\t</audio>\n</figure>\n<p>Some more examples can be found here: <a href=\"https://soundcloud.com/beatsbygan\">https://soundcloud.com/beatsbygan</a></p>\n<h4>Interpolation demonstration</h4>\n<p>The proposed system learns to map points in the latent space to the generated waveforms. The structure of the latent space can be explored by interpolating between points in the space. For the following experiments, the GAN was trained with a latent space dimensionality of size 3.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/blog/static/abcdf884a02358c27af3c85260b3b2db/4f20b/z_space_fig.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 55.4054054054054%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"z_space_fig\"\n        title=\"z_space_fig\"\n        src=\"/blog/static/abcdf884a02358c27af3c85260b3b2db/fcda8/z_space_fig.png\"\n        srcset=\"/blog/static/abcdf884a02358c27af3c85260b3b2db/12f09/z_space_fig.png 148w,\n/blog/static/abcdf884a02358c27af3c85260b3b2db/e4a3f/z_space_fig.png 295w,\n/blog/static/abcdf884a02358c27af3c85260b3b2db/fcda8/z_space_fig.png 590w,\n/blog/static/abcdf884a02358c27af3c85260b3b2db/efc66/z_space_fig.png 885w,\n/blog/static/abcdf884a02358c27af3c85260b3b2db/c83ae/z_space_fig.png 1180w,\n/blog/static/abcdf884a02358c27af3c85260b3b2db/4f20b/z_space_fig.png 8097w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Figure 2: Interpolation in the latent space for kick drum generation. Kick drums are generated for each point along linear\npathsthrough the latent space (left). Paths are colour coded and subsequent generated audio appears across rows (right).</p>\n<h5>A to B interpolation</h5>\n<p>In the following examples, two generated drum samples are selected and their latent vectors are noted. A linear path of 30 steps between each latent vector is created and a waveform is generated for each of those 30 steps.</p>\n<p>Interpolating between Snare A and Snare B.</p>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Snare A</figcaption>\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/a530c5adc630412cbafb582a4cc37a56/snare_a.wav\">\n\t</audio>\n</figure>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Snare B</figcaption>\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/436abd619027e297afffb21117d89034/snare_b.wav\">\n\t</audio>\n</figure>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Linear interpolation</figcaption>\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/faf86ce4aa364ad5424af46d953ca334/demo1_interpolate.wav\">\n\t</audio>\n</figure>\n<p>Interpolating between Kick A and Kick B.</p>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Kick A</figcaption>\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/dfe0b4a25ea3859eddc8f668916957e3/kick_a.wav\">\n\t</audio>\n</figure>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Kick B</figcaption>\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/742442e55da50c7beabcd1fdfc0c7734/kick_b.wav\">\n\t</audio>\n</figure>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Linear interpolation</figcaption>\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/a84f8ea9acfa079a2770691a2c29f4d2/demo2_interpolate.wav\">\n\t</audio>\n</figure>\n<p>Interpolating between Cymbal A and Cymbal B.</p>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Cymbal A</figcaption>\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/09841e4a0aec0a946f1486c0360ab0f0/cymbal_a.wav\">\n\t</audio>\n</figure>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Cymbal B</figcaption>\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/1fbc99f06215f2f1496022fd8a81cdc5/cymbal_b.wav\">\n\t</audio>\n</figure>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Linear interpolation</figcaption>\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/6ab3a48087e0a5f184d4acbb2cd752c0/demo3_interpolate.wav\">\n\t</audio>\n</figure>\n<h6>Linear interpolation</h6>\n<p>More examples of linear interpolation between two random points.</p>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Kick drums </figcaption>\n    \n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/91e38211312e8f1e33148df293864b50/kick_1.wav\">\n\t\t\n\t</audio>\n\t\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/40f30076dbbf42b945c41bf4d105c9b1/kick_2.wav\">\n\t\t\n\t</audio>\n\t\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/7253d959070caea814ef7a240578375f/kick_3.wav\">\n\t\t\n\t</audio>\n\t\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/5d1d324756302d150585ae08cdab10eb/kick_4.wav\">\n\t\t\n\t</audio>\n\t\n</figure>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Snare drums </figcaption>\n    \n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/96f71139fa5188892df7c6daa6f85a89/snare_1.wav\">\n\t\t\n\t</audio>\n\t\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/1e02e4d4fcd56ef58a4e99669b80ff93/snare_2.wav\">\n\t\t\n\t</audio>\n\t\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/b9baef55403470ee47fed7644d07a531/snare_3.wav\">\n\t\t\n\t</audio>\n\t\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/5e311d1c040555f78e5f9b8bda36286c/snare_4.wav\">\n\t\t\n\t</audio>\n\t\n</figure>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Cymbals </figcaption>\n    \n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/7d7c525d3c042a5ea5c93e2b6b2ca98d/cymb_1.wav\">\n\t\t\n\t</audio>\n\t\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/4718bc478ebb9e9c83a3d4e64218a950/cymb_2.wav\">\n\t\t\n\t</audio>\n\t\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/cb6ed75330cc5d300345e5822d905b6d/cymb_3.wav\">\n\t\t\n\t</audio>\n\t\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/b8949068dcd7d2e133de3860fdd11e77/cymb_4.wav\">\n\t\t\n\t</audio>\n\t\n</figure>\n<h6>Spherical interpolation</h6>\n<p>Examples of spherical interpolation between two random points.</p>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Kick drums </figcaption>\n    \n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/cff98ed211a008978d87b3483b11d861/kick_1.wav\">\n\t\t\n\t</audio>\n\t\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/2c3c967e0ef020c81973e2a56ccdb49b/kick_2.wav\">\n\t\t\n\t</audio>\n\t\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/5e977d0c0ea3fb0238ae576d406ff789/kick_3.wav\">\n\t\t\n\t</audio>\n\t\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/9a60b2965bcdf3201a5bab8513206e5a/kick_4.wav\">\n\t\t\n\t</audio>\n\t\n</figure>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Snare drums </figcaption>\n    \n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/e882fc4a27160f9a21eb1f831189fc7b/snare_1.wav\">\n\t\t\n\t</audio>\n\t\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/5786fa5f7d910e03879402574ab7ea73/snare_2.wav\">\n\t\t\n\t</audio>\n\t\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/3663c4a2d0e89348b433a72cb3e2f2c1/snare_5.wav\">\n\t\t\n\t</audio>\n\t\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/d32b01d0be791c6b34361accbbae8186/snare_4.wav\">\n\t\t\n\t</audio>\n\t\n</figure>\n<figure>\n    <figcaption>Cymbals </figcaption>\n    \n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/e36eb151bc142c5b74cedcea4747a651/cymb_1.wav\">\n\t\t\n\t</audio>\n\t\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/3bbd32695a9a772fc1b275f5cc07ea8f/cymb_2.wav\">\n\t\t\n\t</audio>\n\t\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/ec0000da4ddaa7c264f6b298890b255e/cymb_3.wav\">\n\t\t\n\t</audio>\n\t\n    <audio controls\n\t\tsrc=\"/blog/e302009306600dc87defe2ed2a3bd608/cymb_4.wav\">\n\t\t\n\t</audio>\n\t\n</figure>","frontmatter":{"title":"Adversarial Synthesis of Drum Sounds","date":"July 26, 2020","tags":["gans","drumsynth","dafx"],"description":"Adversarial Synthesis of Drum Sounds","thumbnail":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":4.864864864864865,"src":"/blog/static/06749f591793d3fcccf92232de58d679/3c17d/brief-system-overview.png","srcSet":"/blog/static/06749f591793d3fcccf92232de58d679/e0491/brief-system-overview.png 180w,\n